<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-724-570  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 724 570.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Macworld  Sept 1990 v7 n9 p85(6).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Surveying the shakeout; is another Jasmine in the works?andO;(competition among disk drive manufacturers)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Branscum, Deborah.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Fierce competition and narrow profit margins are causing ashakeout among Macintosh hard disk manufacturers, with severalcompanies ceasing operations or filing for bankruptcy.andP;  Some firmsare founded quickly by executives who confuse profitability withcash flow and go under when revenues decline.andP;  Price wars make itdifficult for vendors to provide the level of service and supporttheir customers expect.andP;  Companies that sell at rock-bottom pricesworry competitors, who claim that the price-cutting vendors cannotlive on their margins and are 'shakeout candidates.' Quality,support, and price are issues for consumers to weigh when choosinga drive.andP;  Drives using the same mechanism can vary in qualitybecause 'rejects' from demanding, top-tier customers are resold toconsumers.andP;  Potential buyers should determine service turnaroundtime and how much repairs cost after the drive is out of warranty.andO;Some dealers are knowledgeable in choosing which drives to carryand select only those that are tested rigorously.andP;  Buying throughdirect sales usually means accepting long-distance support.andO;Microtech International is honoring warranties on drives made byJasmine Technology Inc, which is undergoing Chapter 11reorganization.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Financial StabilityCompetitionHard DiskHardware Vendors.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>